{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c100ec64-02c3-487a-8186-2b6aea7daa62","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"157d8d20-2b0a-4738-b9f4-816c5f38ba8c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question about test framework APIs. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":348,"requestId":"BD00:E210B:1F50487:22FA281:6A07C4BD"},"id":"8e3f1806-861f-41f1-8fad-c53d1fc945c1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:13:40.134Z","parentId":"126a82ea-ecfe-46df-880e-38c755cd9499"}
